## üé® Phase 2: Documentation Design & SEO Best Practices

### 2.1 Technical SEO & Discoverability
- **Header Hierarchy**: Each article MUST have a single `<h1>` with keyword-rich subheadings (`<h2>`, `<h3>`).
- **Meta Descriptions**: Include a 150-160 character summary at the top of every markdown file for the Help-Doc search engine.
- **Alt Text**: Every screenshot must have descriptive alt-text for accessibility and indexability.

### 2.2 Visual Documentation Workflow
- **Embedded Screenshots**: Do not just show the screen; explain the workflow *while* the user looks at the image.
- **Annotation Focus**: Use callouts for "Directed Learning" badges in the Student App and "Ready for Execution" status in the Admin Panel.
- **Fidelity**: Capture the "Premium" look (glassmorphism, vibrant gradients). If it looks simple, you have failed.

### 2.3 Structural Efficiency (Atomic Documentation)
- **Shared Components**: Do NOT duplicate documentation for features shared by all roles (e.g., Account Settings, Login, Profile Editing).
- **Referencing**: Write shared features once in a `Shared Activities` section and link to them from role-specific guides.

